---
import SampleLayout from '../../layouts/SampleLayout.astro';
---

<SampleLayout
	title="Sample user guide: New navigation launch in Q4 2023"
	description="Sample user guide By Arnaud Hervy demonstrating clear instructions and visuals for a new navigation launch."
	keywords="technical writing, user guide, sample, navigation, instructions, software, documentation"
	canonicalPath="/samples/user-guide/"
	backHref="/portfolio/user-guide/"
	ogTitle="Sample user guide by Arnaud Hervy: New navigation launch in Q4 2023"
	ogDescription="See how Arnaud Hervy can make complex changes easy to understand with this sample user guide."
	ogImage="/assets/user-guide.webp"
>
	<h1>Find features after the navigation update</h1>

	<p>The navigation has changed. This guide helps you:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Find features after the navigation change</li>
		<li>Complete common tasks without relearning the interface</li>
	</ul>

	<h2 id="new-nav-overview">Overview of the new navigation</h2>

	<p>Use this overview to understand where key elements moved in the interface.</p>

	<picture>
		<source srcset="/assets/new-nav-overview.webp" type="image/webp" />
		<img
			src="/assets/new-nav-overview.png"
			alt="Overview of the new navigation"
			width="1200"
			height="662"
			loading="lazy"
			decoding="async"
		/>
	</picture>

	<h3 id="new-top-nav">New top navigation menu</h3>
	<p>
		Use the top navigation menu on all pages (1) to access key sections. Breadcrumbs make it easier
		to navigate through pages and know where you are.
	</p>
	<h3 id="quicker-page-access">Quicker page access</h3>
	<p>Directly jump to any page in one click (2). No more clicking through menus!</p>
	<h3 id="quicker-dashboard-access">Quicker dashboard access</h3>
	<p>
		Use filters (2) to view course info, user stats, and more. Switch from the Content to the Stats
		view (3) to access dashboards directly from the homepage and group pages.
	</p>
	<h3 id="workspaces">Organized workspaces</h3>

	<p>Keep things organized with two workspaces (4):</p>
	<ul>
		<li>From the home workspace, you will access objects related to all groups.</li>
		<li>From the group workspace, you will access objects related to the selected group.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>View user stats</h2>
	<p>
		On the homepage or any group page, select the <strong>Users</strong> filter to view user stats.
	</p>
	<video
		controls
		loop
		muted
		playsinline
		preload="metadata"
		poster="/assets/new-nav-user-stats-poster.webp"
		width="1200"
		height="772"
		aria-label="User stats filter demonstration"
	>
		<source src="/assets/new-nav-user-stats.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
	</video>
	<h2>Access dashboard data</h2>
	<p>Administrators, Coaches, Authors, and Owners can now:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>view any course, user, program session, and more directly from the homepage,</li>
		<li>and switch to the "Stats" view to view quick insights.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<video
			controls
			loop
			muted
			playsinline
			preload="metadata"
			poster="/assets/new-nav-chips-poster.webp"
			width="1200"
			height="772"
			aria-label="Dashboard data access demonstration"
		>
			<source src="/assets/new-nav-chips.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
		</video>
	</p>
	<p>If you are a learner, your homepage and group pages remain unchanged.</p>

	<h2>Find reports in the new navigation</h2>
	<p>Reports are now located in a different section. Follow these steps to find them:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>On the homepage, select the <strong>All</strong> filter.</li>
		<li>Switch to the <strong>Stats</strong> view.</li>
		<li>Open the <strong>Custom Reports</strong> tab.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>From this page, you will be able to create reports and view saved reports.</p>
</SampleLayout>
